# `@costly/components` Is Read-Only

**Never change files under `packages/components/`.** This includes generated `Component.tsx` files, wrapper `index.tsx` files, layouts, `tailwind.config.js`, barrel exports, and package config.

## Why

The package is synced from [Subframe](https://subframe.com). Local edits drift from the design system and are overwritten on the next `bun sync`.

## How to update UI primitives

1. Change the design in Subframe, then sync:

   ```bash
   cd packages/components && bun sync
   ```

2. Use the Subframe MCP / skills (`design`, `develop`, `install`) when adding or changing components in Subframe — not hand-edits in this repo.

## Where to put customizations

| Need | Do this instead |
| --- | --- |
| Component behavior or styling tweaks | Wrapper in `apps/frontend/src/components/` |
| Page layout / composition | `apps/frontend/src/routes/` |
| App-specific Tailwind overrides | `apps/frontend/tailwind.config.js` (extends `@costly/components/tailwind-config`) |
| One-off className adjustments | Pass `className` at the call site in the frontend |

## Rules

- Do not edit, create, or delete files in `packages/components/` unless the user **explicitly** asks to sync from Subframe or run the Subframe CLI — and even then, prefer `bun sync` over manual file edits.
- Do not add `// @subframe/sync-disable` wrappers in this package — build frontend wrappers instead.
- Import from `@costly/components` in the frontend; never copy component source into apps.
